  "text": "Stack clash protection implementation in GCC spans across multiple layers. The generic stack clash mitigation is implemented in gcc/explow.cc with the core functions anti_adjust_stack_and_probe_stack_clash (line 2072) and anti_adjust_stack_and_probe (line 2201). These functions are declared in gcc/explow.h (lines 74, 78) alongside support functions like compute_stack_clash_protection_loop_data. The implementation uses a target hook TARGET_STACK_CLASH_PROTECTION_ALLOCA_PROBE_RANGE defined in gcc/target.def (line 6535) to allow architecture-specific customization. The default implementation is provided in gcc/targhooks.cc (line 2747) and declared in gcc/targhooks.h (line 305). The option -fstack-clash-protection is defined as a common compiler flag in gcc/common.opt (line 3054). For x86_64 targets, the i386 architecture backend provides output_adjust_stack_and_probe and output_probe_stack_range functions, declared in gcc/config/i386/i386-protos.h (lines 102, 103) and invoked from machine description patterns in gcc/config/i386/i386.md (lines 27827, 27837). The i386 configuration also includes prologue/epilogue stack checking definitions in gcc/config/i386/i386.h (lines 1646-1652). Top-level compiler code in gcc/toplev.cc manages the flag_stack_clash_protection variable initialization (lines 1655-1666). The configure system in gcc/configure.ac provides build-time options for setting default stack clash protection guard sizes (lines 880-902). Comprehensive test coverage is provided in the i386 testsuite: stack-check-11.c through 19.c test various compilation scenarios with different optimization flags, stack-clash-protection.c, and PR-related tests (pr84128.c, pr83994.c, pr84064.c). Test framework support is provided in gcc/testsuite/lib/target-supports.exp with the check_effective_target_supports_stack_clash_protection procedure (line 13634). Documentation is maintained in gcc/doc/tm.texi (line 3772), gcc/doc/tm.texi.in (line 2998), and gcc/doc/params.texi (lines 705-722) describing the target hook and configuration parameters."
}

